description: For sale: $639,900. Large, private ½ acre, wooded lot with custom Hagen Brothers house in desirable West Bloomington neighborhood. Traditional floor plan with finished lower level walkout. Main floor black inlaid marble and travertine tiled floors. Kitchen and all four baths updated tiling and granite counters. Four large bedrooms upstairs, including private master suite. LL guest bedroom, large entertainment area and bar, and separate theater. Spacious living areas with custom built-inn and hardwood throughout.Master balcony, main floor deck, walkout level 3 seasons porch with hot tub for relaxing soaks. Back yard, with fire pit and viewing deck for secluded sunrises, feels like being at the cabin without the drive. 3 car garage with new epoxy floor, and full-sized storage area under the garage for indoor kid fun or future man cave. Private living with plenty of walkable, close outdoor activities, abundant wildlife, trails to Bush Lake, Hyland Park Preserve and quick access to shopping and freeways.

description: For sale: $709,900. Executive walkout two-story home in the prestigious southwest Bloomington neighborhood of Kenmare Shores. One of a kind property on an acre lot with views of the Minnesota River Valley situated on a cul-de-sac. Be impressed with the views from the large deck, sunroom, screened porch and/or two balconies. Main level includes a white enameled kitchen, main level office, dining room, living & family room. The spacious lower level is perfect for those entertainers with a wet bar, wood-burning stone fireplace and large amusement room ready for games tables or a theater space. Over 700 sq ft Spancrete heated workshop can be accessed from the lower level or steps from the garage. Paver driveway, paver patio with a basketball hoop in the backyard. Pet door to fenced in backyard from a caged area in lower level workshop.

For sale: $127,000. Come call this wonderful third-floor unit home in Bloomington! Enjoy modern touches throughout alongside spacious rooms, a wood burning fireplace, an expansive balcony, in-unit laundry, fantastic storage, and great amenities. Minnesota winters no longer have to be dreaded thanks to your parking spot in the heated garage. Stay cool in the Summer at the shared outdoor pool or host a celebration with friends and family in the amusement room. You will also find miles of walking and biking trails just a short distance away that circle around and through Hyland and Bush Lake! Nearby shops and restaurants are an easy drive from your front door. Don't miss the opportunity to call this great place home!

description:
For sale: $725,000. Enjoy beautiful sunrises from this stunning two story with lower level walkout home in the Hillcrest Lakeview Farms neighborhood in West Bloomington.
This home features four season sun room designed for your complete recharge and relaxation. Experience  breathtaking views of the Bush Lake park and Bush Lake beach from almost every room of this house!
This home features a tasteful dining room and a functional white enameled center island kitchen with formal and informal breakfast areas. New wine cooler. Maple floors on the main floor. Andersen windows, high quality Zebra shades throughout the house. 
Four great size bedrooms upstairs open up to great panoramic views of the West side of Bush lake.  
Fifth bedroom option or office space downstairs. Spacious entertainment room with wood fireplace and bar area in the walkout level. Recent addition of teak and cedar sauna in the lower level with 3/4 marble tile shower.
All of this and a desired location in the Twin Cities!

description: For sale: $1,595,000. Set on a gorgeous 1.68 acre site overlooking Anderson Lakes, this custom designed home radiates with light and stunning views of woods and rolling lawn. Convenient to freeways, yet a peaceful respite.

description: Recently sold: $149,900. One level living in this third floor, corner unit condo in W Bloomington. Close to Hyland Lake Park and easy access to Hwy 169. This home offers a great open concept, kitchen with HW floors, SS appliances. The living room has a wood-burning fireplace. Large balcony off the dining room that allows for an electric grill and seating. Full bath off the main entry hallway and in-unit washer/dryer. The large Master bedroom will fit a king-size bed and dresser space. Two large closets lead into the 3/4 master bathroom with a walk-in shower. Second balcony off the master bedroom. Great space! The second bedroom will easily fit a queen size bed with plenty of closet space. The unit includes a storage locker on the same floor, one car space in the heated underground garage and use of the outdoor pool and party room. Water, sewer, trash and cable TV service included in the association dues. New Pella windows and sliding glass door!

Recently sold: $430,000. Spacious 4 level split located in a prime location and on a cul-de-sac. Spacious kitchen with tons of storage that can also accommodate a large kitchen table for entertaining.  aGenerous sized foyer that you don't find in most splits. Three bedrooms on one level and private master suite with 3/4 bath! Upper level bathroom totally re-done in 2019.  Lower level features 4th bedroom with huge closet and large family room! Huge laundry area with a lot of storage as well! Fully fenced yard with plenty of space to play! No backyard neighbors and lots of mature trees! Poplar Bridge Elementary, Olson Middle & Jefferson High School (as of 1/14/2020). Great home with plenty of space to entertain!

description: Recently sold: $145,000.

Recently sold: $184,900. Rare find in Devonwood-2 BR/2 BA+den main floor unit-no steps! Secure covered entry, 1,344 sq.ft. & 1 car garage. Updated w/in the last 10 yrs: kitchen (cabinets, flooring, appls, etc.) HWH, windows, blinds, CT porch floor, beautiful stone flooring in both BA, closet doors in 2nd BR, furnace '07, roof 2019. Big dining room open to the den & living room. Corner wood burning fplc & french doors that open to the porch. (Open the french doors & you have an extra room when entertaining in the warmer months). Huge MBR w/walk-in closet, MA bath w/dual sinks, beautiful marble stone floors, sep. shower & tub. The main bath has the same easy care flooring & a nice vanity. The bright eat-in kitchen o'looks the green spaces D'wood is known for. There's tons of counter & storage space plus a convenient door to the 3-season porch. The laundry room has shelving, there's a linen closet & front coat closet. The 2nd BR has a huge full wall closet. Enjoy the 2 Devonwood outdoor pools & nearby parks!

description: Recently sold: $379,000. This gorgeously landscaped yard creates a tranquil setting that you don't often find. The home capitalizes on nature at every turn. The broad sweeping open-floor concept is highlighted by the updated large kitchen, center island, and surrounding great room spaces. You'll find tasteful updates throughout, unique architectural windows, newer flooring, newer light fixtures, and all of it immaculately clean. Can you imagine having morning coffee on this tree-top deck, listening to the birds chirp? How about entertaining with friends having an evening beverage on the handsome stone patio surrounded by nature? The tucked away 3 season screened porch provides an additional space to enjoy the breeze without pesky insects. Walk to Bush Lake or hop on you bike to Hyland Park Preserve and you are truly away from it all. Ready for the City? Minneapolis is 10 minutes away and Eden Prairie Center is just 5 quick minutes from this secluded gem.

description: Recently sold: $249,900. Rarely available Parkview Highlands townhome! Location and layout make this an amazing place to call home! Kitchen is bright and welcoming! New refrigerator, microwave, and gas stove! Great informal dining room off of the kitchen that opens to the living room with a wood burning fireplace. Master bedroom has vaulted ceilings, private master bath and walk-in closet. Laundry on upper level along with 2nd full bath and 2nd bedroom. Lower level is freshly painted and features new carpet! Lower level has a family room and 2 flex rooms for an office or craft room along with another 3/4 bath. Lower level finished space is a real bonus in this development. Enjoy all of the nearby parks, golf, trails, shopping options and restaurants! Dred Scott is out your back door and has baseball, soccer, picnicking, playground area, softball, tennis, volleyball, and The Links, an 18 hole putt putt golf course. This home is a must see!

Recently sold: $250,000. Desirable first floor unit at MN Valley Club Condo facing southeast over wooded land. This unit includes a sun porch and deck, gas fireplace, in unit laundry and a private master suite. Storage room is conveniently located on same floor as condo unit. Shared amenities include assigned underground parking, car wash, indoor pool, exercise room, party room, large outdoor patio and overnight guest suite.

Recently sold: $328,000. Great home at a great price located in high demand West Bloomington neighborhood on a quiet street. Quick and easy access to Hwy 169 and 494. Four beds with two flex rooms in lower level that you can easily convert to make six bedrooms. Don't let the snow fool you  - this home has a great back yard with a large deck, upgraded vinyl coated full fence, and large storage shed with poured concrete floor! Grand fireplace in lower level family room leading to walkout.  Prime location close to the shopping, restaurants, parks, schools, etc. Don't miss out on this one!!

Recently sold: $367,500. Stop to see this beautiful 2-story in Bloomington's Countryside neighborhood. Enjoy the open kitchen, dining & family room on the main walking out to the new patio. Hardwood floors throughout the main and new carpet on the upper level allow you to move right in. 4 spacious bedrooms await you on the upper level with updated bathrooms. The master bedroom has access to storage space above garage which can be turned into a large walk-in closet. description:
Recently sold: $255,500. Amazing 3 bedroom 2 bath home situated between Anderson lake and Bush lake. An abundance of natural light from large windows, skylights & french doors in this open floor plan home with spacious kitchen with a pantry. Eat-in dining area and large living/dining room. 2-story wood-burning fireplace with optional 3rd bedroom or in home office loft overlooking the living room brings more natural light and lots of built-in-storage. Each of the two bedrooms has an attached bathroom, one has french doors leading out onto a screened in porch. Minutes away from many parks & lakes including Hyland park reserve, Richardson Nature center, Anderson & Normandale Lakes. Bloomington School District.

Lease Terms: Seeking a 12 month lease term or longer. $2150 Security Deposit. All utilities are the tenants responsibility including snow and lawn care. Pets may be accepted based on owners approval with a $300 non-refundable pet fee. This home does not qualify for Section 8.

Rental Screening Guidelines:
Background and Credit Checks are conducted on all adults
Income of 3x the monthly rent or more
Credit score of 600 or higher (under 600 can be considered with a double deposit)
No felonies or violence related criminal convictions
No previous evictions

The criteria above are not all inclusive and other factors may apply, it is only meant to be a guideline. 
Unique home with amazing features nestled between Anderson lake and Bush Lake!

description: Recently sold: $165,000. Countryside neighborhood Gem! 3BR/3BA rambler on a quiet tree lined street in a much desired neighborhood! Large addition off the back of the home in 1997 that created a large open dining and living room area with a gorgeous gas fireplace and many windows looking out into a private fenced in yard! Enjoy time in the screened in porch, gardening in the back yard, or entertaining. Kitchen remodel in 2004 and includes a fabulous eat-in kitchen space and plenty of cupboards and storage. Master Bedroom suite with walk-in closet and private 3/4 master bath! Lower level features 3rd bedroom with egress window, 3/4 bath, family room, and amazing workshop! The Seller took great care in all of their improvements over the years, work was done by professional contractors throughout. New roof (2017) and A/C(2019). Award winning Bloomington Schools (Normandale Elementary, Olson Middle,and Jefferson High). close to freeways, shops, restaurants and parks. Location, Location, Location!

Recently sold: $324,000. To schedule a showing, contact Dan Francis at 760.449.8961 or DMF9688@gmail.com

BRINGING THE OUTSIDE INSIDE

Newly renovated 4Bed/2Bath home in much desired West Bloomington neighborhood. Enjoy the best of living in the woods and in the city. Great natural light, bringing the outside inside. Forest scenery from windows and deck off of main living area. Hiking trailhead immediately across the street. Yet, easy access to retail, parks, malls, restaurants, health care, and more.

- Single family home

- Split level. 2 bed, 1 bath, and living space in each level
- Open floor plan, great for hosting
- South facing windows inviting a lot of natural light
- Amazing deck with forest views

description: Recently sold: $332,000.

Recently sold: $325,000. Talk about living near a park, well, this feels like you're living IN the park - Privacy, yet great proximity to Highland Park Reserve - with enough snow, you could cross county ski from your front door to the Park trails! Gorgeous spread of perennial gardens in front & back yard, deck, patio, screen porch - it's all right here to take in and Enjoy this summer still! Sellers have a lot of pride in this home they've owned for 26 years! Contemporary and spacious kitchen renovation add-on in 1995 - wonderful southern exposure, beautiful views of back yard, and tons of storage and space for cooking! Hardwood floors and woodwork has been well maintained, main floor bathroom renovated professionally plus basement bathroom added. New windows 2001, furnace/AC 2004, roof 2015, driveway new in 2017... with many rooms freshly painted this June. This is a great opportunity in a gorgeous location near the park, with higher end unique homes surrounding. West Bush Lake Rd is a gorgeous drive home!

description: Recently sold: $460,500. Immaculate 4BR/4BA Colonial two-story nestled on a beautiful oversized high demand West Bloomington lot! Many upgrades throughout, pride of ownership shows! description: Recently sold: $194,900. Beautifully maintained townhome. New counter tops & painted cupboards, new carpet, furnace & A/C only 1 year old, freshly painted throughout, large master bedroom w/walk-in closet, & new roof & siding.

Recently sold: $165,000. This main level two-bedroom condo is the largest design of the Devonwood Village Homes. Immediately upon entering you will feel its natural light, openness and spacious appeal. Welcoming eat-in kitchen opens to a formal dining area on one side, and a peaceful screened patio on the other. The large living room is accented with a gorgeous oak and marble fireplace. 

Adjoining the master bedroom, a large double-sink master bath comes with a separate tub and walk-in shower. An open den awaits your creative possibilities between the master and second bedroom. The second full bathroom is nicely equipped with a tub/shower combo. With your security in mind, guests alert you before you allow their entry to the building.

The condo is in a great neighborhood in West Bloomington, and it is close to Dred Scott Fields with tennis, basketball, volleyball courts, softball fields and mini golf. Also, nearby are the Minnesota River Valley Wildlife Preserve, Hyland Lake Park Reserve, Bush Lake Park and several golf courses. Two heated in-ground swimming pools and walking trails are right on the property.

description:
Recently sold: $215,000. Kari Anderson and REI Real Estate & Property Management are excited to present this beautiful four bedroom, one and a half bathroom duplex in West Bloomington. The home is located in a cul-de-sac so there is minimal traffic! Inside you will find lots of room and also updated, clean and modern decor. With 1,900 square feet, the living room is spacious and leads to the kitchen which has white cabinets and matching stainless steel appliances. There is a half bathroom on the main level, a huge garage and stairs leading to the finished basement. The space can be used for a bedroom as it recently had an egress window installed. If you do not use it for a bedroom, it can easily be used as a family room, playroom, office, den or for storage. There is a patio door from the kitchen area to the back yard as well. Once you go upstairs to the upper level, you will find some built-in cabinets in the hallway, three more bedrooms and a full bathroom. The townhome is located near many parks, schools, highways, shopping destinations and restaurants such as Cape Fusion, Zeke's and El Loro Mexican Grill. Pets to be considered with an additional deposit. Some breed and weight restrictions may apply. Tenant covers utilities, lawn care and snow removal. Applications are $45 per adult.

Tenant covers all utilities, lawn care and snow removal.
